<paragraph blockId="3.[151,924,1725,1789]" box="[151,367,1762,1789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">
<figureCitation box="[151,257,1762,1789]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStart-3="FIGURE 4" captionStart-4="FIGURE 5" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,919,943]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionStartId-2="4.[151,250,1781,1805]" captionStartId-3="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionStartId-4="6.[151,244,1420,1444]" captionTargetBox-0="[172,1404,233,853]" captionTargetBox-1="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetBox-2="[195,1392,526,1749]" captionTargetBox-3="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetBox-4="[199,1350,190,1370]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@2.[160,1428,181,895]" captionTargetId-1="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetId-2="figure-186@4.[189,1398,522,1755]" captionTargetId-3="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetId-4="figure-17@6.[189,1398,179,1394]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionTargetPageId-3="5" captionTargetPageId-4="6" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. The phylogenetic relationship among Drymadusini species from China inferred from the COI-ND2 concatenated fragments. Rooted by Gampsocleis sinensis, the tree was constructed by Maximum likelihood (ML) with GTR+G4+F model. Topology supports of all major nodes are indicated above branches in this order: the SH-aLRT value, and the bootstrap value." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Wings of male Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A. tegmina; B. left tegmen in dorsal view; C, right tegmen in dorsal view; D. hind wings; E. left tegmen in ventral view; F. right tegmen in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." captionText-3="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." captionText-4="FIGURE 5. Body of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A, B. male; C, D. female. A, C. dorsal view; B, D. lateral view. Scales: 1 cm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683474" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683478" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683482" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5683474/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5683478/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/5683482/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Figs. 1–5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[269,285,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[194,1391,187,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[189,1398,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Living Ptosoproctus species. A, B. P. lanzhouensis sp. nov.; C–F. P. baishishanicus sp. nov. G. habitat of P. baishishanicus at Baishi mountain; H. Michael Lee collecting P. baishishanicus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683490/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[297,367,1762,1789]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 14" captionStart-1="FIGURE 15" captionStartId-0="16.[151,250,1935,1959]" captionStartId-1="17.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox-0="[215,1397,329,1902]" captionTargetBox-1="[201,1396,606,1395]" captionTargetId-0="figure-60@16.[189,1398,309,1912]" captionTargetId-1="figure-209@17.[189,1398,594,1399]" captionTargetPageId-0="16" captionTargetPageId-1="17" captionText-0="FIGURE 14. Time signal oscillograms. A–C. Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov.; D–F. Ptosoproctus baishishanicus sp. nov.; G–I. Eulithoxenus emeljanovi. Dashed lines: above which are the fragment expanded in the next picture." captionText-1="FIGURE 15. Distribution map of Eulithoxenus emeljanovi and the species of genus Ptosoproctus gen. nov. The symbols with a point inside are previous records." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683500" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683502" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5683500/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5683502/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">14–15</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1834,2041]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="552" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1834,1860]" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Description.</emphasis>
General. Body small. Head frons flat, slightly oblique (
<figureCitation box="[912,979,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
AB). Fastigium of vertex distinctly wider than scape of antenna (
<figureCitation box="[414,504,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Eyes broadly round and projecting outward. Disc of pronotum both sides with a broadly obtuse concavity on middle part, anterior and posterior margin of pronotum slightly concaved, median carina and posterior transvers sulcus obscure, central transvers sulcus distinctly Chinese characters “八”-shaped, lateral carina faintly indicated; lateral lobes longer than high, with weakly humeral sinus (
<figureCitation box="[1149,1214,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
BCEF). Prosternum unarmed (
<figureCitation box="[264,354,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum with a pair of obtuse triangular lobe-shaped processes, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1424,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="551">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Metasternum with a pair of arched lobe-shaped processes, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1097,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of fore coxae with 1 long spine; length of fore femora nearly equal to pronotum, dorsally unarmed, ventrally with 0–2 internal spinules and externally unarmed, genicular lobes with 1–2 internal spinules and externally unarmed; fore tibiae both sides with a crack-shape tympana, dorsally with 3–4 externally spines and internally unarmed, ventrally with 6 pair of spines, a pair at the apical. Middle femora dorsally unarmed, ventrally with 0–1 internal spinules and externally unarmed, genicular lobes with 1–2 external spinules and 1 internal spinule; middle tibiae dorsally with 4–5 internal spines and 2–4 external spines, ventrally with 6 pair of spines, a pair at the apical. Hind femora dorsally unarmed, ventrally with 0–1 external spinules and 2–3 internal spinules, genicular lobes with 0–1 spinules on both sides; hind tibiae dorsally with 23–34 spines on both sides and 1 pair of apical spurs, ventrally with 8–12 spines on both sides and 2 pair of apical spurs.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683478" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5683478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="552" startId="4.[151,250,1781,1805]" targetBox="[195,1392,526,1749]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1781,1842]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1781,1805]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
Wings of male 
<taxonomicName authority="Shen &amp; Yin &amp; Lee &amp; Liu &amp; He &amp; Wang &amp; Wang, 2021" authorityName="Shen &amp; Yin &amp; Lee &amp; Liu &amp; He &amp; Wang &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2021" box="[441,712,1782,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Ptosoproctus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanzhouensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[441,712,1782,1806]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[719,801,1782,1806]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[719,801,1782,1806]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A. tegmina; B. left tegmen in dorsal view; C, right tegmen in dorsal view; D. hind wings; E. left tegmen in ventral view; F. right tegmen in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1887,2022]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="553" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">
Male. Tegmina brachypterous, slightly shorter than pronotum, slight beyond or extending to 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1253,1266,1887,1901]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite posterior margin. Left tegmina ventrally with stridulatory file about 30 teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1151,1924,1950]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,526,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-186@4.[189,1398,522,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wings of male Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A. tegmina; B. left tegmen in dorsal view; C, right tegmen in dorsal view; D. hind wings; E. left tegmen in ventral view; F. right tegmen in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Right tegmina ventrally with vestigial stridulatory file about 19 teeth (
<figureCitation box="[672,759,1960,1986]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,526,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-186@4.[189,1398,522,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wings of male Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A. tegmina; B. left tegmen in dorsal view; C, right tegmen in dorsal view; D. hind wings; E. left tegmen in ventral view; F. right tegmen in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). Mirror on right tegmina pentagonal, distinctly longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[223,290,1996,2022]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,526,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-186@4.[189,1398,522,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wings of male Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A. tegmina; B. left tegmen in dorsal view; C, right tegmen in dorsal view; D. hind wings; E. left tegmen in ventral view; F. right tegmen in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
CF). Hind wings rudimentary (
<figureCitation box="[644,736,1996,2022]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,526,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-186@4.[189,1398,522,1755]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wings of male Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A. tegmina; B. left tegmen in dorsal view; C, right tegmen in dorsal view; D. hind wings; E. left tegmen in ventral view; F. right tegmen in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683478/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). 10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[786,799,1995,2009]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite fused with epiproct, posterior margin of 10th abdominal tergite with a broadly triangle notch at the joint, form a strongly down-folded membranous projection on tergite posterior margin, apex broadly rounded, almost sightless from above, projection with a median longitudinal furrow which basal narrow and apical widish. Cercus pileous, short and stout, external margin almost straight; apex short and obtusely conical; inner tooth near cercus apex, robust, recurved, wide at base, gradually narrow towards the apical part, apex acute, raise first and then decurved. Subgenital plate about 1.25 times longer than width, with lateral carinae, middle part of posterior margin with a weak triangular excision, styli short (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Titillators with broad basal arms, apical inflated connect with short apical arms; apical arms dorsally bearing one rows denticles, with acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[565,652,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">
Female. Tegmina slightly shorter than quarter pronotum, extending to 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1023,1036,438,452]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite anterior margin, clearly visible and discontiguous in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[714,782,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[193,1395,418,1555]" captionTargetId="figure-126@3.[189,1398,414,1558]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head and thorax of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–D. male; E, F. female.A. face; B, E. head and pronotum in dorsal view; C, F. pronotum and tegmen in lateral view; D. thorax in ventral view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683476/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
EF). Cercus conical and hirsute (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1247,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). 10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1296,1309,474,488]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite not fused with epiproct, posterior margin of 10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[766,779,510,524]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite with a shallow broadly round notch on middle part (
<figureCitation box="[299,386,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate wider than length, with lateral carinae, middle of posterior margin with a deep angle concave (
<figureCitation box="[386,477,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor shorter than hind femora, distinctly upcurved (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1234,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1928,1952]" captionTargetBox="[197,1391,782,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-299@5.[189,1398,774,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdominal apex of Ptosoproctus lanzhouensis sp. nov. A–E. male; F–H. female.A, F. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C, G. ventral view; D. rear view; E. titillators; H. ovipositor. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683480" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683480/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,618,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="553">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body laterally and dorsally generally whitish gray, with dark brown or black marmoration, ventrally yellowish (greenish in life). Lower and hind margin of pronotum lateral lobes whitish gray with dark brown spots. Tegmina orange, costal area whitish gray with dark brown spots, radius area with dark brown spots. Spines of each leg black. Apex of male cercus inner tooth black. Ovipositor apical part black.
</paragraph>
